llowing the employees to watch dan hands through shadowing can allow them to see a different way of thinking.\n\nCEO: Shadowing is a good start, STUDENT. The case does mention Dan\'s extensive client interaction, which could be valuable for others to observe. However, you\'ve also highlighted the need for standardization. **How can we ensure that shadowing Dan, who relies on intuition and experience, leads to standardized processes rather than simply replicating his individual approach, which is precisely what we need to move beyond for scalability and franchising?**\n\nSTUDENT: time is up\n\nCEO: STUDENT, thank you for meeting with me. I am glad you were able to study this case and share your insights. I hope our conversation was challenging yet helpful. **Would you be willing to provide feedback by answering a few questions about our interaction?**\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Great! On a scale of 1 to 5, how helpful was our conversation in your thinking through this case situation? (1=not helpful, 5=extremely helpful)\n\nSTUDENT: 5\n\nCEO: Thank you. What did you **like most** about this simulated conversation?\n\nSTUDENT: It gave me real life questions to think through\n\nCEO: That\'s helpful. What way do you think this simulated conversation **might be improved**?\n\nSTUDENT: sometimes the process was repetative\n\nCEO: It has been a delight talking with you today. **Would you be willing to let me pass this conversation transcript to the developers to help improve the simulated conversations for future students?** The conversation will be completely anonymized (your name will be removed). This would be **a big help** in developing this AI chat case teaching tool .\n\nSTUDENT: yes\n\nCEO: Thank you for your time, STUDENT. Goodbye and have a nice day. I am going to turn this over to the AI Supervisor to give you feedback.') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE created_at=VALUES(created_at),student_id=VALUES(student_id),score=VALUES(score),summary=VALUES(summary),criteria=VALUES(cr